# A cross-unit-element collection construction `(List of: dep.Type)` passed as a
# constructor ARG. The element (xunit_listelem.widget) is cross-unit, so the
# typechecker must resolve it to mint the List_widget mono + stamp the construction
# node -- else the emitter emits `/* unhandled callee List */0`. Mirrors zparser's
# main building a ZVfs with `(List of: zvfs.ProviderBox)`. A binding `ws: (List of:
# T)` would NOT reproduce (it emits via the declared-type path, not emitEmptyColCreate).
main: function is {
    b: xunit_listelem.Bag items: (List of: xunit_listelem.widget)
    print "n=\{b.count}"
}
